A Bash Script is a series of commands saved in a file and can be executed to achieve a desired result. Bash Scripting is mostly used for automation of tasks. Bash Script is created by doing the following steps. Create a file touch random.sh. Go into the file and type #!/bin/bash enter #write your comment: this script echoes hi naomi enter echo hi naomi. Use the command ls -l random.sh chmod u+x random.sh run the ./random.sh command